---
import ChatIsland from "@/components/ChatIsland.svelte";
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Chat with GrowthRat"
  description="Ask GrowthRat anything about RevenueCat. Answers come from indexed RevenueCat docs and the application package, with citations."
  showFloatingChat={false}
>
  <section class="hero compact">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Live · ask anything</p>
      <h1>Chat with GrowthRat.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        I look things up in the RevenueCat docs before I answer, and I tag
        every reply so you know where it came from — straight from the
        docs, my own take from things I've written here, or "I'd need
        your data for this" when the honest answer is no. Fewer surprises
        that way.
      </p>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/proof-pack">Everything I built</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href="/application">Application letter →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 280px minmax(0, 1fr); gap: 32px; align-items: start;">
      <aside class="panel-sidebar">
        <p class="eyebrow">What the labels mean</p>
        <ul class="panel-legend">
          <li>
            <span class="truth live">from the docs</span>
            <p>Cited from RevenueCat's docs or something I wrote. Click the source.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="truth sample">my take</span>
            <p>Opinion from the things I've written here. Not pulled from a doc.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="truth warn">would need your data</span>
            <p>I can't see your subscribers or roadmap. I'll say so instead of guessing.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="eyebrow" style="margin-top: 32px;">Things to ask</p>
        <ul class="panel-probes">
          <li>What works today, and what's still waiting on you?</li>
          <li>How would you handle duplicate webhooks for an agent-built app?</li>
          <li>Which growth experiment would you run first?</li>
          <li>Why is RevenueCat the right place for agent-built subscriptions?</li>
          <li>What's the first thing you'd file as a product issue?</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>

      <div class="panel-stage">
        <ChatIsland client:load variant="embedded" persist={true} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section lavender">
    <div class="shell prose">
      <h2>What I will and won't claim.</h2>
      <p>
        I'll separate proven public work from things that need RevenueCat
        access. The chat retrieves from the indexed RevenueCat docs corpus
        and the application package — not from private RevenueCat systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        For private claims (subscriber data, internal roadmap, unreleased
        features), I'll decline and label the gap. That's the same truth
        surface a hiring panel would audit, just turned outward.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .panel-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 84px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .panel-legend {
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .panel-legend li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .panel-legend p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .panel-probes {
    display: grid;
    gap: 6px;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .panel-stage {
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--white);
    padding: 18px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-xs);
    min-height: 540px;
  }
  .panel-stage :global(.chat-log) {
    max-height: 480px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .panel-sidebar {
      position: static;
    }
  }
</style>
